&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Saw a neat open-source project on Twitter/X — a P2P webcam built on WebRTC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repo: &lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/ShouChenICU/WebCamera" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://github.com/ShouChenICU/WebCamera&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looked through the code and docs — interesting enough to deploy and try. Sharing notes below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="project-overview"&gt;Project Overview
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;WebCamera is a network webcam tool built on WebRTC, developed with Nuxt.js and managed with Yarn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="features"&gt;Features
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-time video: WebRTC-based, efficient streams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-platform: Works across browsers and devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dev-friendly: Built on Nuxt.js, easy to extend and maintain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modular design: Easy to integrate and expand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Privacy &amp;amp; security: Peer-to-peer encrypted connections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
